DevFlow Privacy Policy
Last updated: 31/08/2024
Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how DevFlow ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our application.
1. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information:
GitHub account information (when you connect your GitHub account)
Code snippets and pull requests that you submit for review
Usage data (how you interact with the app)
Device information (operating system, device type)
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide and improve our AI-powered code review service
Customize and enhance your experience within the app
Analyze usage patterns to improve our features
Communicate with you about updates and new features
3. Data Storage and Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. Your code snippets and GitHub data are encrypted in transit and at rest. We do not store your GitHub credentials.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell your personal information. We may share your data with:
Third-party service providers (e.g., cloud hosting services)
Law enforcement agencies when required by law
5. Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to:
Access, correct, or delete your personal information
Opt-out of marketing communications
Disconnect your GitHub account
6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes via email or through the app.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: nootapps+privacy@gmail.com
By using DevFlow, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.